definition: leading/in first place/top of the list
(archaic) sentence-final particle expressing a doubting attitude
to reside/to be (in a certain position)/to store up/to be at a standstill/residence/house/restaurant/classifier for bedrooms
head/chief/first (occasion, thing etc)/classifier for poems, songs etc

sentences.english: The wedding expenses in Shanghai are among the highest in the country.
sentences.chinese: 上海的婚嫁消費成本在全國居首位。

sentences.english: The pesticide poisoning reduced mainly by organophosphate insecticide.
sentences.chinese: 農藥中毒以有機磷殺蟲劑居首位。

sentences.english: Give of your best to the Master;
sentences.chinese: 將你最好的獻恩主，你心讓主居首位。

sentences.english: When it comes to books they want to read, Star Wars titles top the list.
sentences.chinese: 當涉及到他們想要的閱讀書籍，星球大戰列居首位。

sentences.english: Different cultures dominate the other factors in leading to the failure of enterprise incorporation.
sentences.chinese: 在併購失敗的決定因素中，文化的差異性居首位。

sentences.english: Iceland, Nordics top world gender equality list.
sentences.chinese: 全球性別平等度排名，冰島居首。

sentences.english: Efficiency is the dominant idea in many businesses.
sentences.chinese: 效率是許多事業中居首位的觀念。

sentences.english: This canyon heads the list of natural attractions.
sentences.chinese: 這個峽谷在天然美景中居首位。

sentences.english: Be the first in all my work and life.
sentences.chinese: 在我一切的工作和生活上居首位。

sentences.english: The total export of foreign trade leaps to the first.
sentences.chinese: 外貿出口總額躍居首位。

sentences.english: The pesticide poisoning was mainly caused by organophosphorous insecticide.
sentences.chinese: 農藥中毒以有機磷殺蟲劑居首位。

sentences.english: I give You the first place in all things by faith.
sentences.chinese: 藉着信我讓你在凡事居首位。

sentences.english: Be the first in all my service too.
sentences.chinese: 也在我所有的服侍上居首位。

sentences.english: Her novel topped the nation's best-seller list.
sentences.chinese: 她的小說在全國暢銷書名單中居首位。

definition: to follow closely behind sb or sth (idiom)
second only to.../(in second place) preceded only by...
to rank (number 1, or third last etc)/to be among (those who are in a particular group)
lit. only one branch of the tree is thriving (idiom)/fig. to be in a league of one's own/outstanding
to divide into rows/to identify subcategories/to break down into constituent parts/breakdown/disaggregation
notice or announcement/list of names/public roll of successful examinees
